calculateFee(uint256).details: Check the fee amount for a certain duration (in minutes) for renting the bike

checkBike(uint256).details: Function to check on a bike's data
checkBike(uint256).return: lastRenter The last user to have used the bikecondition The condition of the bikecurrentlyInUse The usage status of the bikeusageTime The timestamp of last usage startstate The bike's state

checkBikeStatus(uint256).return: inUse Boolean to tell if the bike is being used or not

checkUser(address).details: Function to check on a client's data
checkUser(address).return: state The client's state (in ride or else)received The amount the client deposited during his last tripreturned The amount the client received back after his last tripnumberRides Trips count goodRides Good trips count

constructor.details: Contract constructor sets the bike Admin address, the fee (by minute) and the necessary deposit

emergencySwitch().return: alarmOn A boolean that blocks function execution if true.

getGoodRides(address).details: Get the rides after which the bike was in good condition
getGoodRides(address).return: goodRidesCount The client's good rides count

getReturned(address).details: Get the total value returned to the client
getReturned(address).return: returnedAmount The client's total returned amount

getTotalRides(address).details: Get the total rides of a client

isBikeFirstUse(uint256).details: Check if the bike is being used for the first time
isBikeFirstUse(uint256).return: isFirstTime True if the bike has never been used, False otherwise

isClient(address).details: Check if some address is related to a client
isClient(address).return: True if the address is a client address

isOwner().return: true if `msg.sender` is the owner of the contract.

renounceOwnership().details: Allows the current owner to relinquish control of the contract.

params.bikeId: The client must input the bike id

rentBike(uint256).return: success Did the renting process succeed ?

params.bikeId: The client must input the bike id

transferOwnership(address).details: Allows the current owner to transfer control of the contract to a newOwner.

params.newOwner: The address to transfer ownership to.

renounceOwnership().notice: Renouncing to ownership will leave the contract without an owner. It will not be possible to call the functions with the `onlyOwner` modifier anymore.
